I"±<p>Sometimes we have multiple groups in the data and we would like to generate a plot for each of the groups. First we import the data set:</p>
<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>psg = pd.read_stata('dta_files/perc_suicide_gun.dta')
</code></pre></div></div>
<p>And then we can plot using the seaborn package</p>
<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>g = sns.FacetGrid(psg, col="statename", col_wrap=3, height=4)
g = (g.map(plt.scatter, "year", "perc_gun", edgecolor="w").add_legend()) # "year" would be on the x axis and "perc_gun" would be on the y axis
for ax in g.axes.flat:
    ax.set_ylim([0,1])  # set the range for the y axis
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(plt.AutoLocator())
    _ = plt.setp(ax.get_xticklabels(), visible=True) # in order to keep track of which group we are referring to
    _ = plt.setp(ax.get_yticklabels(), visible=True)
g.savefig("perc_suicide_gun.jpg") # save the results as a figure
</code></pre></div></div>
